dbook”), written c. AD 100, is one of the most influential works of Stoic philosophy. The Greek text presented here is the first one to be based an a full evaluation of the complete tradition.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn Greek, Ancient (to 1453).0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aConduct of lifevEarly works to 1800. 0aConduct of lifexEarly works to 1800. 0aEdition. 0aEpiktet. 0aEthics, Ancient. 0aStoizismus. 4aEdition. 4aEpiktet. 4aStoizismus. 7aHISTORY / Ancient / General.2bisacsh  aEpictetus.  aStoicism.1 aBoter, Gerard, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Classics and Near East Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110636178oZDB-23-GCN08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2007z9783110277135oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET ALTERTUM 2007z9783110277005oZDB-23-DGD0 cprintz978311019503340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311092642240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110926422423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110926422/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGDb2007  aZDB-23-DGGb2007  aZDB-23-GCNc2000d2014